caption: Very nice. Great service. The taste is different from the pad Thai on the location on California Ave.  That's the only reason I gave 4 and not 5 star. The sushi is a little smaller too. Thai iced tea is sooo good!!
The spicy udon is to die for. In the winter I get takeout from Jaiyen at least once a week. Great food and run by nice people.
Great food great presentation.
Favorite Thai place in the city. Great Pad Thai and their sushi is really delicious and well presented. Friendly staff and very good prices.
So tasty and reasonably priced! Love it!
This place is fantastic. The food is wonderful and the staff is so nice. Definitely coming back to try all the combinations of noodles and toppings.
Super nice people and the sushi is really great and very affordable!
The best panang curry!
I enjoy both locations. The Sweet Potato roll is so beautiful and delicious

I have ordered from here three times during COVID and every time has been excellent quality for the value paid.  They have daily special coupons you can use and the food has tasted very good everytime over a variety of menu items.  Will keep coming back!

Ordered lunch to go online. Had special requests for everything. They did everything exactly how I asked. Flavors were really good. Good size portions for a lunch special. Really reasonable prices too. Will return.
Good food. Awful smell of sewage inside. Only take food to go. Do NOT eat in.
So good!!

This is my first time trying it and I lived It. The roles are very fresh, the soup was delicious and my green bubble tea was a perfect desert. I’m all about supporting local businesses (especially during this uneasy times) and I will Definitely be back for more and hopefully dine in there soon.

Ordered delivery, I live 6 minutes away from the restaurant. And hour and a half went by so I called them to check on it and was told someone will deliver my food shortly. When the food finally arrived every single thing was cold.
Good food, really good service. Really recommend any of the noodle dishes.

Deep Fried Spicy Tuna starter was really good and had a nice amount of spice/kick.  Not hot but very complementary.  The Thai Spicy Basil with Tofu, unfortunately. was pretty bland.  Good, but they ought not promote it as a "spicy" dish.  I've order here before and remember feeling the same with other "spicy" dishes I've had.  The sushi we've had is excellent and maybe they're more about that.  But, other than the tuna starter from last night, the "spicy" is really hard to detect.
Great local sushi!  And BYOB!
Delicious food, relaxed and friendly environment, I will be revisiting often!

Fantastic food, I usually get there sushi, but the other day I got their curry and it was awesome. Its BOYB which is cool, my friends and I brought our own sake. The service is always great and friendly.
mixed experience, two of my party enjoyed our meals, but the two others found their meat too tough/underseasoned.
My favorite local sushi place. BYOB!
This place is excellent and broad, the menu was enchanting and the prices were very fair. fast, productive service and very welcoming staff. I highly recommend this place.
Amazing neighborhood Thai and Japanese place. The sushi rolls come out incredibly tasting and beautiful!
Good service even in busy time. Taste and flavor great. Chicken was a bit hard but not bad. Bathrooms and overall feel was little casual.

This is unquestionably one of the most pleasant place to eat in the region. Whenever I come to this place I am exceedingly glad. They maintain their very high  level service and the topmost level of food  they give. You can never go wrong with this place. Very  recommended.

I used to love this place but after the whole reno they did a few years back it just went a bit downhill. I think the management is new as well, but might be wrong. Anyways, what strikes you  the moment you walk in is the smell. I can’t figure out what exactly it is.. could be the grease from the kitchen or sewage.. or both.. nothing pleasant anyways. The food is usually good, although communication with staff is not easy. My favorite are chef’s rolls (giant, dragon and a few more I don’t remember now). Spicy mussel appetizer is a must. Delicious!
Delicious and affordable! Fast staff the crab rangoon melted in my mouth the rolls were awesome and soup is on point
Great food, great prices
I love this place! They are reasonably priced. The staff is super nice and attentive. And look at how cute the set up is! I totally recommend the sushi!!

Might not be the most authentic sushi, but the food is good, staff are friendly.. unfortunately the odour (can’t figure out, either grease or sewage) in the shop is unbearable! I’ve been there 3 times, in the past few months, and no improvement on the smell.
Sushi and sashimi was good as was the veggie fried rice. Service was very nice. Green tea is fresh and tasty. We'd stop back if we're in the neighborhood.
Tasty food, good prices, friendly staff
Great food
Our favorite local sushi spot!

What's the point of ordering online and setting up a delivery time if the restaurant doesn't even abide by it? I placed an order this morning for an order to be delivered at 11:45am. The restaurant was closed, but the ordering system ON THEIR OWN WEBSITE allowed me to place the order. It's now 20 minutes past the 11:45am delivery time, so I call the restaurant and they say that it's going to take up to another 30 minutes for the food to arrive? And I feel that's if we're lucky - I'm not holding my breath.  Other than the terrible ordering process, the food is pretty good. I guess the moral of the story is don't order Jai Yen online if you expect to get your order in a timely fashion.
Great food, great quantity, great price.
Great sushi!

Decent sushi restaurant close to home.  Always good no matter what dish I order.  For dinner it gets quite busy just after 6.  Service is good and they always keep the water and iced tea filled.  Price wise, it is on par with other sushi restaurants around the area.
Wonderful and delicious food and service.
Stop by yesterday. I love sushi and this place has become my favorite stop!! Excellent food, presentation, atmosphere and service!

I love this place! I was skeptical about "sweet potato sushi" and a friend ordered it. It became one of my faves. Their lunch specials also cannot be beat, and I have been going to this place for years.

I came here on a date and the whole restaurant had a strange smell to it. On top of that, the small restaurant was dominated by a noisy group of 12 seated in the direct center of the dining room. The sushi was decent but small in comparison to the price. If you're craving sushi, maybe check it out and get the order to go if necessary.
Lovely lunch specials. Good food and good service. BYOB, but no corkage fee.
Super food super service
Always consistently good

Relaxing. Attentive server. Clean. Sporty atmosphere.

We cannot remember the last time we were so disappointed in a restaurant’s food and service quality. Along with the fact that we were the only customers seated in the restaurant, it was an all around disappointing experience.
Excellent sushi, crab rangoon, and warm meals!
Good food, great service
Food is great!!! Service is great!!! Japanese people in the restaurant business are so courteous; unlike Chinese restaurant people. And I am Chinese!!!
Beautifully decorated sushi plates and good noodles.

Excellent restaurant with wonderful food. Great quality and flavor, good value lunch specials, friendly staff and very nice decoration! The degree of care they put in decorating their food is surprising for how not-expensive this place is. Recommended!
Ok food but not like it used to be before the remodeling

This is my sushi spot to go . Usually the sushi is well made and firm but this last time it was just soggy. It was falling appart and i couldnt taste any flavor except the soy sauce.  I definately will give them another shot, because usually they are solid.

Nice place!  I had the spicy stir fried udon noodles and kappa maki rolls, and my friend ordered the turtle roll.  I loved the presentation, and the food was delicious.  Great service as well.  Will definitely go back!
This is one of the few Thai places that I recommend to friends and family.
I've eaten there a few times and the food is good. The prices are very reasonable. And the portions large
Food was good the service was great.

Excellent sushi. Lunch special is yummy.

I love this place. My boyfriend suggested it and I love the atmosphere but they didn't have fortune cookies . But the food was awesome !!!!
My favorite local spot. The pa se ew is solid and the shitake maki is very surprising.
Delicious!

Food is reasonably priced and some of the best tasting sushi in the area. The Tropical and Baby Bear are highly recommended. Pleasant quiet atmosphere, good for date night or casual BYOB dinner with friends
The Hawaian fried rice to die for!!!

The food is always delicious! The service is great and very friendly. Tonight I left my phone on the table! No worries. My server ran down the street after me to return it! Just one more reason to love Jai Yen :)
My favorite sushi place! The seaweed salad is amazing!!!
Best sushi in the city, and we've had a lot. Try the sweet potato roll.
I liked it. The food is tasty and place is usually quiet.
My favorite Japanese restaurant, fresh sushi clean and great friendly service as a plus it's BYOB.  Well priced.
Great place to buy a Groupon from! Total treat yourself meal 🤓🤓🤓

Every single time I go here I leave happy. I read other people's reviews, first if you are ordering sushi to be delivered, that's your fault. You are doing something very strange and if it arrives cold I really can't feel bad for you. Unless you have no legs get off your tush and walk in. If you have no legs, well. If it's diabete's related I'm not sure you should be eating fried sushi anyway. I half a mile from here, and I live a block from Nano Sushi, and yet I take the extra couple blocks walk and pay the extra dollar or two each and every time. You can taste where that dollar goes. The fish is always fresh, every ingredient is always perfect and the presentation is always worth a picture. At this stage I've tried nearly everything on their menu, if it sounds like something you would like, then more than likely you will like it. The BYOB pertains to beer and wine, and there is a 711 a block down the street if you needed such. No liquor. So you know.  I've once waited 8 minutes for a table and that happened on a Friday night, other than that the place is always semi slow. Which is nice as they help you immediately and feed you as quick as possible. I honestly cannot say how fortunate I am to live so close to my favorite sushi restaurant, and that it is affordable and consistently perfect.  I could do without the music. Why I am forced to listen to blaring techno at a dimly lit sushi bar is beyond me, I suppose it is the edge of boys town so I let it slide. Also, I dislike the desserts, but that is an across the board thing. Their food blows our mind if you want cheese cake go to the cheese cake factory.
Used to be so good. Now the rolls are meh, atmosphere is absurd... but at least it's BYOB.
The spicy tuna rolls made me lose my appetite. But the service and other food I ordered was great.
Will definitely go back.
Nice atmosphere 10 minute walk from Wrigley Field. Super tasty Thai at very reasonable prices.
Good food.  It is pricey but quality

I normally have a very good experience at Jai Yen and am (or was) a regular customer.  That changed today.  I called to place a very simple order for delivery and the woman I spoke with was incredibly difficult to communicate with.  I had to give her my order and information several times.  She repeated the order back to me and said it would be 45 minutes to an hour for delivery.  I asked how long it would be for pick-up and she just kept repeating 45 min to an hour which made absolutely no sense to me.  But we hung up and I waited the hour to receive my order.  When I finally got it, it was wrong.  Despite repeating the order back to me, she entered it incorrectly.  I called to get it corrected and again, she couldn't communicate at all.  She kept repeating that I would get a "credit" but could not articulate how it would work.  There was no offer to bring me the correct order and no apology.  I asked to speak to someone else (literally anyone else) and she said she is the only person there.  Again, this makes no sense to me.  I worked in food service for several years and usually have a lot of patience (things go wrong sometimes and that's okay) but this was just unacceptable.  Will not be returning.

Met a friend here for lunch a while back. The makimono rolls here are pretty good. They have a good variety from very simple (how they are in Japan) to the more westernized versions with varied ingredients. The staff was great and the interior space is colorful. The different aquariums are a nice touch.
Great Sushi
Great rolls, large sashimi, reasonably priced (great lunch specials).
Great sushi and a great value. The rolls are much larger than the other sushi places in East Lakeview. BYOB too! Couldn't recommend enough.
My go-to place for sushi, pad thai, and filipino lumpia!  I appreciate their pan-Asian options.  Everything is tasty!
My favorite sushi place so far. Get the Dynamite. Delicious:)
Rolls are tasty, miso soup is good! ☺
Little crowded, but great sushi!
It was food, I ate it. Not the best, not the worst. Maybe it would be better if I ate in. But for the price, I wasn't impressed :(
It's good. Nice environment, good food. BYOB too. Have come here with the girl a couple times, nothing toooo fancy but nice enough for wine and dinner

You can take 20% off your first order online by mentioning this from their website. This is a a BYOB and they have two locations that you can enjoy some high quality sushi  You can find this on a ocasionally Groupon website
Beat sushi ive ever had! Highly recommend coming here

This is by far my favorite sushi restaurant in the city. I love sushi and trying new places but I always end up here. The rolls are super fresh and thir staff is extremely kind! I love this place and will continue to come back for my spider rolls :)
Yum!

I really like this restaurant. +1 BYOB and no corkage fee! +1 Groupon/Yelp/LivingSocial deals are always available! +1 Good sushi (difficult to achieve), my favorite is the Dynamite roll paired with a smaller roll like spicy tuna or salmon. My fiance likes their Beef Pepper Steak. Also the crab rangoon isn't too shabby. +1 Staff is friendly and pretty attentive. They also have an outdoor sidewalk area when it's warm out. In the fall, they still have it setup with those tall fire heaters. Never a line to get seated and not a far walk from the Red Line. I usually like to come here about once a month.
Extremely overpriced. 37 dollars to get 2 sushi roills and a bubble tea to the door?
Good food, good service.  Slight mixup when ordering Salmon Roe we got a Salmon Roll.  Would eat again.

Great Sushi, Good service and Good atmosphere.  Come for lunch (carryout) and sometimes for dinner(dine in). Would come for breakfast but you can't eat sushi for breakfast I am told. Staff is attentive always remembering my usual orders and recommending specialty rolls.

The rolls here are pretty amazing. They strive to be unique in their choices of ingredients in each roll and it pays off. They have really tasty rolls. Be sure to try to Dragon and Rainbow rolls.  The portions are fairly substantial. 2-3 rolls should be good for 2 people, depending on how hungry you are. The decor is very modern. If you did not look at the menu, you would not think that this is a Japanese restaurant. the service was pretty good despite a full house when I went.  Overall, this place serves up decent Japanese fare with a twist, at a decent price for an enjoyable meal.

I had a really great experience here. The first time I tried this place was through pickup. The food was great and plenty for the price. I noticed the place was well decorated and decided to go in on another occasion to dine in.  I was very happy with the quick and friendly service as well as how quickly the meals were prepared for me. I ordered the Spicy Miso Soup, Spicy Salmon Roll, and Fried Rice. No regrets and well worth the price. Again, the place is well decorated and made the whole experience enjoyable.

I thought I'd give this place try since I was able to get a gift certificate for disounted price.  That was the WRONG choice.  It was simply one of the worst Thai food I've ever had and trust me, I have been to enough Thai restaurants in the city.  I should have figured since 3/4 of the menu is Japanese and the remaining is Thai.  I ordered the spicy udon noodles with chicken, chicken panang curry, tom kha with shrimp, spicy tuna hand roll, and spicy squid maki.  Everything minus the sushi was sub-par.  If it weren't for the decent sushi, I would have given this place 1 star.  The worst of those dishes was the spicy udon noodles.  It was disgusting.  I took 1 bite and could not go for a second one and didn't even bother to take it home (Yes, it was that bad).  The service too was sub-par to mediocre.  We were seated at a table with no utensils, water was not refilled, and server took a while to bring back our credit card receipt EVEN though my husband went and paid at the counter which usually means people are in a hurry to leave.  Upside is it is BYOB and the decor and music are pretty good.  I really wanted to like this place but sadly I will not be returning to this place.

This is a review of the Belmont/California location, which has been open for a year or so and is just what the neighborhood needed - a top-notch casual sushi/Thai restaurant where there isn't one. This place is walking distance from my house and I've never been disappointed. I love noodle dishes and sushi, and Jai Yen does an excellent job with both. Prices are very reasonable and service is speedy and friendly.

I stopped in for some sushi. I got a spicy tuna and the spider roll. I think the food was fine, but it didn't blow me away. I also wasn't all the satisfied with the spider roll, to be honest; it tasted a little fishy, but i'm not sure whether that was a sauce they added or not. I may stop in to get my sushi fix, but I'm not sure how often I'll really be stopping by. Hopefully, you'll enjoy it more than i did. The atmosphere was nice though. The spicy miso was yummy.

I like Jai Yen. It isn't the best food. But is perfectly fine. What is really nice is the value. For every $20 you get a free california role, so I usually get a bunch of things, save a pad thai for lunch for the next day, and then get my free roll and have a feast. Really fast, pleasant staff, overall just very very solid.
Delicious and BYOB, cannot complain!

The sashimi and sushi portions are very generous.  They are always fresh and presented like a high end sushi place would, nit at a much more reasonable price.  The gyoza and hatasaki appetizers are very good starters.  The waitstaff are very friendly and attentive.
